title: 256bit encryption algorithm
extract: Rijndael is a family of ciphers with different key and block sizes. ... It supersedes the Data Encryption Standard (DES), which was published in 1977. The algorithm described by AES is a symmetric-key algorithm, meaning the same key is used for both encrypting and decrypting the data.
extract_html: Rijndael is a family of ciphers with different key and block sizes. ... It supersedes the Data Encryption Standard (DES), which was published in 1977. The algorithm described by AES is a symmetric-key algorithm, meaning the same key is used for both encrypting and decrypting the data.
